title.rendered: Gujarat vs UP, India Women’s League 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Gujarat pushed Harleen Deol to No.6 in the last game, playing Sabbhineni Meghana at No.3.

Gujarat: Sophia Dunkley, Laura Wolvaardt, Sabbhineni Meghana, Ashleigh Gardner, Dayalan Hemalatha, Harleen Deol, Sushma Verma (wk), Kim Garth, Sneh Rana (c), Tanuja Kanwar, Ashwani Kumari

UP: Alyssa Healy (c & wk), Devika Vaidya, Kiran Navgire, Tahlia McGrath, Grace Harris, Deepti Sharma, Sophie Ecclestone, Simran Shaikh, Parshavi Chopra, Anjali Sarvani, Rajeshwari Gayakwad

Pitch Report

Venue: Brabourne Stadium, Mumbai

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 166

2nd innings average score: 162

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Also Read:

India vs Australia, 3rd ODI: Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Ashleigh Gardner’s venue stats are – in the literal sense of the word – staggering. She is the highest wicket-taker (14) and the second-highest run-scorer (234) at the Brabourne Stadium, achieving all this in a mere seven games.

In the previous clash between these franchises, Kim Garth (five for 36) and Sophie Ecclestone (two for 25 and 22* off 12) were the captain and vice-captain of the Best11 respectively. Moreover, Sophie is the only player from both teams to feature in the Best11 in all games of the edition.

Laura Wolvaardt’s recent form deserves a special mention. She has scored six fifties in the last seven outings – of which two have come at the venue in consecutive innings

Barring the opening game, Harleen Deol has not let fantasy players down, providing points one way or the other: 198 runs, a wicket, a catch, and a run out.

Tahlia McGrath has provided bonus points for a thirty once and a fifty twice, scoring the second-most runs (180 at 45) for UP.

Kiran Navgire and Grace Harris’ only fifty of the season came against Gujarat.

Alyssa Healy has been smashing runs at the Brabourne Stadium with ease and comfort, registering scores of 58 and 98* this season and ending up as a power player on both occasions.

Dayalan Hemalatha has managed a mere 44 runs at 11 in her last five outings.

In the last three games at the venue, all five fifties were scored by the top four batters and 22 of 37 wickets belonged to spinners.
